-- Hungary Stocks: OTP, E-Star Alternative Are Active in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-03-30T15:40:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/hungary-stocks-otp-e-star-alternative-are-active-in-budapest.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock index
rose 0.1 percent to 18,635.67 as of the close in Budapest. The
gauge has advanced 9.8 percent this year.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  E-Star Alternativ Nyrt. (ESTAR)  (ESTAR HB), a Hungarian energy
company, fell to the lowest in more than 2 1/2 years after
posting a net loss for 2011. The shares dropped as much as 11
percent and last traded 3.6 percent lower at 2,940 forint, a 32
percent decline in the first three months of 2012 after a 37
percent drop in the last quarter of 2011.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, fell 0.6
percent to 3,829 forint after rising as much as 1 percent as
European finance ministers increased rescue funds. The stock
jumped 19 percent this quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
